      <p class="- topic/p ">The battery capacity test estimates the available battery runtime
by temporarily reducing the rectifier output to discharge the batteries.
When the test is completed the rectifier output automatically returns
to the defined level.</p>
      <note type="important" class="- topic/note ">It is recommended to perform the battery capacity
test (with the designed load) to evaluate the current condition of
the batteries.</note>
      <note class="- topic/note ">The automatic switch over to battery operation does not interrupt
the output.</note>
      <p class="- topic/p ">To start the battery capacity test:<ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Make sure the batteries are fully charged and the rectifier
is running in float charge.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Hash key</b> to enter the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">User stack</b>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Use the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Arrow keys</b> to navigate until the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> show <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Battery capacity test :xxx</codeph>, where “xxx”
is the runtime of the last test in minutes.<fn class="- topic/fn ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">If a test is interrupted
or no test has been performed before, the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> will show <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Battery capacity test :???</codeph> instead of the runtime from the
last test.</p>
                  </fn>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Clock/number 1 key</b> to start the test. The <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> now shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Batt. operation time &gt; ...min</codeph>. <note class="- topic/note ">The remaining runtime will only be shown if advanced battery
monitor is installed.</note>
               </p>
               <p class="- topic/p ">If you need to interrupt the test
while it is running, press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Back key</b> to stop the test. An
interrupted test will not give any test result.<note class="- topic/note ">If a mains fault
occurs during the test, the test will end immediately without any
test result.</note>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">The test is completed when the display shows <codeph platform="PxW WxW" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Normal operation load power ...%</codeph>
                  <codeph platform="SDC" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Float charge load ...%</codeph> and an alarm has been
activated.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">To view the result of the test:<ol class="- topic/ol ">
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Hash key</b> to enter the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">User stack</b>.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Use the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Arrow keys</b> to navigate until the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> show <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Battery capacity test :xxx</codeph>, where “xxx”
is the runtime of the last test in minutes.<fn class="- topic/fn ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">If a test is interrupted
or no test has been performed before, the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> will show <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Battery capacity test :???</codeph> instead of the runtime from the
last test.</p>
                           </fn>
                        </p>
                     </li>
                  </ol>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Back key</b> or wait 30 seconds to exit the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">User stack</b>.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </p>
